This paper discusses active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper focuses on theoretical guarantees for the performance of active learning in the version space, which is a concept in computational learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since active learning is commonly used in these fields. The paper also discusses the use of kernel methods, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), so cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses optimization techniques, which are relevant to many areas of computer science, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category.
